			</td><td width="2%">&nbsp;</td><td width="44%"> Abstract
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: Given the importance of agriculture, knowledge of pesticide use in small family farms proves to be essential.  The main goal is to analyze the level of awareness regarding pesticide use in family farms with a view to assessing potential flaws in the control of the chemicals. The procedure adopted for this project was based on literature and begins with the definition of essential elements such as: the concept of pesticide and its use in Brazil and around the world, its positive and negative effects, control of pesticides, legal aspects, the concept of family farming and the analysis of the level of awareness regarding the use of pesticides in small family farms. The methodology results from a descriptive process, which, in association with book reports and bibliographical survey, provided an abundant source of information. It was observed that pesticide control is possible through registration in federal government agencies, being its sale conducted by skilled professionals through prescription. Despite the measures mentioned, the misuse of the substance due to poor knowledge and inefficient inspection by the government are a reality. Other problems result from pesticide smuggling in Brazil and the inadequate use of personal protection equipment. It is imperative that the family farmer be encouraged to learn more about the use of chemicals in their property as to better assess the pros and cons of pesticide use. Thus, the present research proves to be thorough regarding the study of pesticides, based on specific legislation provided by the Constitution, as well as enlightening and encouraging for providing a discussion on the positive and negative aspects of pesticide use, showing the need for more investment in research and more commitment by the government, provided that the study is relevant to all society.					<B>Objectives</B>: he present paper aims to present positive and negative aspects of pesticide use as well as the measures taken by public authorities to ensure that mandatory requirements provided by law are satisfied					<B>Methods</B>: The main goal is to analyze the level of awareness regarding pesticide use in family farms with a view to assessing potential flaws in the control of the chemicals. The procedure adopted for this project was based on literature and begins with the definition of essential elements such as: the concept of pesticide and its use in Brazil and around the world, its positive and negative effects, control of pesticides, legal aspects, the concept of family farming and the analysis of the level of awareness regarding the use of pesticides in small family farms. The methodology results from a descriptive process, which, in association with book reports and bibliographical survey, provided an abundant source of information. It was observed that pesticide control is possible through registration in federal government agencies, being its sale conducted by skilled professionals through prescription. Despite the measures mentioned, the misuse of the substance due to poor knowledge and inefficient inspection by the government are a reality. Other problems result from pesticide smuggling in Brazil and the inadequate use of personal protection equipment. It is imperative that the family farmer be encouraged to learn more about the use of chemicals in their property as to better assess the pros and cons of pesticide use. Thus, the present research proves to be thorough regarding the study of pesticides, based on specific legislation provided by the Constitution, as well as enlightening and encouraging for providing a discussion on the positive and negative aspects of pesticide use, showing the need for more investment in research and more commitment by the government, provided that the study is relevant to all society.					<B>Results</B>: 					<B>Conclusion</B>: 				</P>
